src:
Osam golova Partizana, igrali Vulićević, Trobok, Dinga…
06 Nov 2019, 19:19 by Milos
Prvi tim Partizana nalazi se u Mančesteru, gde će u četvrtak, 7. novembra od 21 sat igrati meč četvrtog kola L grupe Lige Evrope protiv Junajteda na Old Trafordu.
U međuvremenu Mozzart sport prenosi, da su drugopozivci i omladinci, predvođeni novim trenerom Teleoptika Albertom Nađom, odigrali su prijateljski meč protiv člana Druge Beogradske lige ekipe Rakovice i slavili sa 8:0.
Debitovao je sin Gorana Troboka Dmjan, a prilku su dobili i Miroslav Vulićević, Dominik Dinga, Milan Smiljanić.
Sastav Partizan u prvom poluvremenu: Slavković, Pešukić, Smiljković, Dinga, Šehović, Smiljanić, Marinković, Stanojlović, Lakčević, S. Jovanović, Gigić.
U nastavku su igrali: Damjanović – Vulićević, Smiljković, Petrović, Trobok, Smiljanić, Marinković, Stanić, Lakčević, Marković, Čapljić.

POVEZANE OBJAVE
text:
Eight Partizan goals, played by Vulicevic, Trobok, Dinga…
06 Nov 2019, 18:19 by Milos
Partizan's first team is in Manchester, where they will play the fourth round of Group L of the Europa League against United at Old Traford on Thursday, November 7th at 9pm.
In the meantime, Mozzart Sport reports that the second-rounders and youngsters, led by new Teleoptics coach Albert Nadja, played a friendly match against a member of the Second Belgrade League of the Rakovica team and celebrated with 8: 0.
Goran Troboka's son Dmjan made his debut, and Miroslav Vulicevic, Dominik Dinga, Milan Smiljanic also got the opportunity.
Partizan squad in the first half: Slavkovic, Peskovic, Smiljkovic, Dinga, Sehovic, Smiljanic, Marinkovic, Stanojlovic, Lakcevic, S. Jovanovic, Gigic.
The following played: Damjanovic-Vulicevic, Smiljkovic, Petrovic, Trobok, Smiljanic, Marinkovic, Stanic, Lakcevic, Markovic, Capljic.
